description:
Alpharetta, USA

### **Please** **note that this is a remote position.**


Do you want to experience the essence of a large organization in a company with a personal touch? Come and work with us! We are looking for creative, innovative, and collaborative people like you to join our team.


### **Take your ambitions to the next level**


The Oracle Cloud ERP AR/Advanced Lead Consultant provides domain, functional and technical expertise required to effectively design and implement solutions on the Oracle Cloud ERP Receivables module.


* Provide techno-functional expertise on projects and initiatives involving Oracle Cloud ERP receivables and its integration with other internal and external boundary applications;
* Identify gaps and present solution options to businesses based on nuances of the Oracle Receivables product and best practices;
* Ensure that all capabilities delivered align with original business objectives, application service levels, IT strategies, and design intent;
* Work with the client’s finance and accounting functions to capture and map business requirements to the Oracle Cloud functionality. Identify gaps and advise clients on options, risks, and value propositions;
* Be accountable for the generation and accuracy of the requirements document and the Oracle Cloud ERP configuration;
* Configure Oracle Cloud ERP as part of the implementation and ensure that the implementation meets the design of the solution and aligns with Oracle Cloud ERP implementation recommended best practices;
* Be accountable for the solution design, configuration and implementation and ensure the implementation is consistent with this design;
* Organize and facilitate functional design sessions with business users from multiple geographical regions and functional areas;
* Integrate requirements from multiple design sessions and teams into the Cloud ERP system design;
* Develop use and test cases to test the implementation of Oracle Cloud ERP and participate in the execution of such test cases;
* Provide support to the testing team and end users during the various test cycles and remediate or dispose of test case failures or anomalies;
* Align departmental policies and procedures with Cloud ERP system processes, policies and procedures in the solution implementation;
* Support the IT solution project execution methodology, report on project progress, and proactively identify and manage issues through closure.

### **When it just clicks!**


Does this sound like you?


* Bachelor’s degree or higher;
* Over eight years of experience in Oracle ERP implementation;
* Thorough understanding of operational financial controls and accounting processes as well as deep functional knowledge of the Oracle Cloud ERP Receivables module;
* Demonstrable experience in participating in Oracle ERP (EBS) implementations as a functional consultant with a minimum of three implementations (at least one implementation with Oracle Cloud ERP Receivables);
* Experience with configuration responsibilities;
* Expert knowledge in financial system integration and overall ERP development, testing and support;
* Demonstrable experience in facilitating and conducting requirement gathering sessions, JAD sessions, conference room pilots, UAT test case development, and oversight;
* Experience gathering requirements, designing, and implementing Receivables, Customer Billing, Payment System Connectivity, Customers, Revenue Management, Credit Management, Cash Management & Banking, and Advanced Collections;
* Experience working with ERP to mature financial processes and reporting;
* Lead experience:


	+ Leading small teams (two to four people);
	+ Leading design sessions;
	+ Creating requirements and design documents;
	+ Creating a parallel testing strategy and approach;
	+ Familiarization with project management methodologies and Microsoft Project.
* Testing and training experience, specifically in helping finance and accounting functions adopt the newly defined procedures;
* Experience in a flexible, innovative, and fast-paced work environment;
* Superior communication skills: written, spoken and presentation, with the ability to communicate and interact with senior and executive-level management and influence outcomes;
* Previous experience in the healthcare/hospital, insurance, or financial services industry is an asset.

Language skills:
* English: Proficient

Toronto, Canada

### **Please** **note that this is a remote position open to candidates across Canada.**


Do you want to experience the essence of a large organization in a company with a personal touch? Come and work with us! We are looking for creative, innovative, and collaborative people like you to join our team.


### **Take your ambitions to the next level**


In this role, you will provide domain, functional and technical expertise required to effectively design and implement HR solutions on Oracle Cloud ERP HCM modules such as Core HR, Employee Self-Service, Manager Self-Service, Absence Management, and Benefits Management.


* Identify business requirements and align them with Oracle Cloud/Fusion HCM functionality;
* Configure the Cloud/Fusion HCM application based on client requirements;
* Provide functional application leadership and guidance to the client on leading practices and the functionality of the software modules through all phases of an implementation;
* Work with the client to develop business solution designs to ensure that business requirements are met;
* Provide thought leadership around industry leading practices for improving operational efficiencies and the profitability of client business;
* Document and perform application set ups in test and production instances;
* Thoroughly review application set up and configuration with the appropriate client lead to obtain sign off;
* Raise issues as they arise and work on resolutions in a timely manner to ensure adherence to the project schedule;
* Work with the respective client functional lead:


	+ to ensure knowledge transfer;
	+ throughout system testing.
* Provide guidance to the respective client functional lead in the preparation of training materials and class agendas;
* Contribute to presales efforts as required;
* Coach and ensure the development of project team members.

### **When it just clicks!**


Does this sound like you?


* BA/BS degree from an accredited college or university in computer science, engineering, or a directly related field;
* Seven years of progressive experience in a consulting environment or related industry experience working directly with Oracle E-Business and Cloud/Fusion applications;
* Five years of related technical, business or project experience;
* Successful experience as an Oracle Cloud/Fusion HCM functional lead on at least three full cycle implementations;
* Proficient in at least three application modules;
* Experience with the business processes in HR modules including HR Core, Recruiting, Talent Management, Digital Assistant, Communicate, Touchpoints;
* Experience with Oracle Cloud/Fusion HCM;
* Ability to:


	+ communicate effectively in both written and verbal formats;
	+ resolve problems in a timely and effective manner, involving project management as appropriate;
	+ successfully manage relationships with clients and colleagues;
	+ effectively produce deliverables;
	+ identify, assess and mitigate relevant risks during bid development and project execution.
* Assets:


	+ French skills.

Language skills:
* English: Proficient
